  "text": "The five key ASan implementation files are:\n\n1. **compiler-rt/lib/asan/asan_interceptors.cpp** (repo: sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d): Implements ASan interceptors for standard library functions (memcpy, strcpy, malloc, etc.). The primary function is `InitializeAsanInterceptors()` which registers all the intercepted functions at runtime startup.\n\n2. **compiler-rt/lib/asan/asan_rtl.cpp** (repo: sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d): Implements the ASan runtime initialization. The primary function is `AsanInitInternal()` (called via `AsanInitFromRtl()` and `__asan_init()`), which sets up shadow memory, initializes flags, installs interceptors, and prepares the ASan runtime. Also contains the `AsanInitializer` class for static initialization.\n\n3. **llvm/lib/Transforms/Instrumentation/AddressSanitizer.cpp** (repo: sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d): The LLVM IR-level pass that inserts ASan instrumentation. The primary struct is `AddressSanitizer` (the core instrumentation logic) and `AddressSanitizerPass::run()` is the entry point for the new pass manager.\n\n4. **gcc/asan.cc** (repo: sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333): Implements ASan instrumentation in GCC as a GIMPLE optimization pass. The primary class is `pass_asan` (a `gimple_opt_pass` subclass) and the key function is `asan_instrument()` which performs the actual instrumentation of memory accesses.\n\n5. **gcc/asan.h** (repo: sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333): The header file for ASan in GCC, declaring the public interface including `asan_function_start()`, `asan_finish_file()`, `asan_emit_stack_protection()`, `asan_protect_global()`, and related HWASan functions."
}

